 and vague declarations that the social world has become financialized, Adkins delivers a precise examination of the relation between finance and society, one that is rich in empirical and analytical detail.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aEconomicsxSociological aspects. 0aFinancexSocial aspects. 0aMoneyxSocial aspects. 0aSpeculationxSocial aspects. 0aTimexSocial aspects. 4adebt. 4afinance and society. 4afinance capitalism. 4afinance. 4amoney. 4asocial formations. 4aspeculation. 4atemporality. 4atime. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360711840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503607118423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503607118.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles